{"lemma":"هِرُّ","slug":"هِرُّ","root":"ه.ر.ر","root_slug":"ه-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41079","n44275","n41081"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cat"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to purr, to whirr, to bray, to grumble, to snarl, to howl","tags":["ambitransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to abhor, to detest, to loathe","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have violent diarrhoea","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of هَرَّ (harra, “to snarl”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"great quantity of water or milk","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of هُرَّ (hurra, “to have violent diarrhoea”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare ه د ر (h d r)."},"ipa":["/hirr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41079","headword_ar":"هَرَّ","root":"hr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yahir~u","text_ar":"يَهِرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hariyrN","text_ar":"هَرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, &c.,) said of a dog, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He snarled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"howled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whined;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he uttered a cry less vehement than barking"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of his little patience of cold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barked and grinned, displaying his fangs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) It is said in a trad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Alkaloba yahir~u mino waraA='i A^aholihi","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الكَلْبَ يَهِرُّ مِنْ وَرَا=ءِ اَهْلِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the dog"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"snarls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harks and grins, displaying his fangs, behind his master:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, that courage is a quality implanted by nature in a man, so that he engages in wars naturally, and from care to defend what should be inviolable, not reckoning upon a reward, like as the dog naturally barks and grins, displaying his tangs, to defend his masters. (L, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hariyrN","text_ar":"هَرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to other sounds than the cry of the dog; as in the instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hariyru Alr~HaY","text_ar":"هَرِيرُ الرّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sound of the turning of the mill-stone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~ati Alqawosu","text_ar":"هَرَّتِ القَوْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bow made a sound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K.) And the looking of courageous men, one at another, is likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hariyr","text_ar":"هَرِير"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISd, Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~a fiY wajohi Als~aAy^ili","text_ar":"هَرَّ فِى وَجْهِ السَّايِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He grinned in the face of the beggar, showing his teeth, and looking sternly, austerely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"morosely"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b4-  [Hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~ahu","text_ar":"هَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yahur~u","text_ar":"يَهُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yahir~a","text_ar":"يَهِرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [the latter irreg., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarim~u","text_ar":"يَرِمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as aor. of the trans. v."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ram~a","text_ar":"رَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~N","text_ar":"هَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hariyrN","text_ar":"هَرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He disliked, disapproved of or hated, him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~ahu Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"هَرَّهُ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his vicinity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~a AlkaAsa","text_ar":"هَرَّ الكَاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaroba","text_ar":"الحَرْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hariyrN","text_ar":"هَرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He disliked."},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the cup of wine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"war."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~ahu Albaroda","text_ar":"هَرَّهُ البَرْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yahur~uhu","text_ar":"يَهُرُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~N","text_ar":"هَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cold made him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a dog) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to snarl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to cry"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the manner described above"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahar~ahu","text_ar":"اَهَرَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ihoraArN","text_ar":"اـِهْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is said in a proverb, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aA naAbK","text_ar":"ذَا نَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N A^ahr~a","text_ar":"شَرٌّ اَهرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was, an evil thing that made the fanged animal to snarl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: alluding to the appearance of the signs and symptoms of evil: the sayer thereof, hearing the cry ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hariyr","text_ar":"هَرِير"},{"kind":"text","text":") of a dog, feared the assault of evil, and therefore said this to denote the magnitude of the case in his mind: meaning, nought but an evil thing made the fanged animal to cry: and for this reason, the use of an indeterminate word as an inchoative is well. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n44275","headword_ar":"هَرَّ","root":"hr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hir~N","text_ar":"هِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drove"},{"kind":"text","text":"sheep or goats:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":3043},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, in S, K, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir","text_ar":"بِر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he called"},{"kind":"text","text":"them. (Yoo, in TA, ibid.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n41081","headword_ar":"هِرٌّ","root":"hr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male cat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~aworN","text_ar":"سِنَّوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K:) which latter is uncommon in the language of the Arabs (IAmb, in Msb, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"snr","text_ar":"سنر"},{"kind":"text","text":";) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hir~apN","text_ar":"هِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A. Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hir~N","text_ar":"هِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter is sometimes called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hrapN","text_ar":"هرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, Msb:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hr~N","text_ar":"هرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hirrpN","text_ar":"هِررةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hir~apN","text_ar":"هِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hirarN","text_ar":"هِرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hir~apN","text_ar":"هِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hurayorapN","text_ar":"هُرَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb))       -A2-  Also, a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"har~ahu","text_ar":"هَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning \"he disapproved of, or hated, him or it. \" (S) It is said in a proverb, (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEorifu hir~FA mino br~K","text_ar":"يَعْرِفُ هِرًّا مِنْ برٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knows not him who dislikes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hates him from him who behaves towards him with goodness and affection and gentleness, and regard for his circumstances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) this is the best explanation of it: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the action of him who grins in his face, showing his teeth, and looking steraly, austerely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"morosely, from the action of him who holds loving communion with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the calling of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the calling of them to water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the driving of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the calling of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats to provender from the calling of them to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar) or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2889},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the driving of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yoo, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the calling of them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yoo, TA.) It has been explained [more fully] in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br","text_ar":"بر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","IAmb","Msb","TA","IAar","Yoo"]}]}}